dc_title_s: Belgii pars septentrionalis communi nomine vulgo Hollandia nuncupata continens statum potentissimæ Batavorum Reipublicæ seu provincias VII Foederatas
dct_provenance_s: Historic Maps copy is from the estate of N.B. Fox, Princeton class of 1899.
dc_description_s: Relief shown pictorially. "Cum privilegio Sac. Cæs. Majestatis." Insets: Batavorum coloniæ Occidental Indiis Septentrionalis Americæ implantatæ -- India Orientalis Batavorum commerciis, potentia & coloniis celeberrima. Includes unlabeled views of New Amsterdam and Batavia. Privilege is below unlabeled view of Batavia. Homann became geographer to the Holy Roman Emperor in 1715. cf. Tooley's dictionary of mapmakers.
